Police in Kano state have succeeded  to come to the rescue of another man popularly known as Ibrahim Lawan who was confined to a room for  good 15 years by his biological father Malam Lawan Sheka Unguwar Fulani in Kumbotso local government area of the state. It was gathered that the  35, years old man was alleged to have been detained by his biological father, Malam Lawan at Sheka Unguwar Fulani adjacent Gidan Mai Unguwa Bello for allegedly becoming truant to his directives for that length of time without allowing him to access to sunlight. The operation was carried out by the State Police Commissioner, Habu  A. Sani alongside the OC Metropolitan Unit of the Police DSP Magaji Musa Majia during the operation, Mallam Lawan, who is a Friday Mosque  Chief Imam, was not at home when the security operatives arrived his  house to free  the victim from his captors. After  Ibrahim was taken away to the police Command at Bompai  however, he was quickly moved to the Malam Aminu Kano Hospital for  Medical checks up in order to ascertain the level of his medical  fitness after a very long time of loneliness and incommunicado. Ibrahim, who was 20 at the time of his detention, was alleged to have become mentally deranged as result of the psychological toture  infringed on him by his parents Leadership recall that Ibrahim is the second person to have been rescued by the Police within 48 hours in Kano state, also a man one  Ahmad was also rescued by the police after he was caged for seven  years by his Father and step Mother for being on hard drugs  consumption  all his life.